<div id="Idea_2534"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2534-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2534">Linux And GNU, Free as the Vendor of Choice&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3914-4049">jabailo</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Today, the best software is freely available on the Web...the Linux OS and GNU applications.<br/><br/>That said, any spending that occurs above and beyond what can be had, at high quality, for free, must be looked at with the utmost scrutiny.<br/><br/>Show me where I can run a search saying "How much did we spend on Desktop Software by the Federal Government in 2009" ?</div>
