<div id="Idea_2521"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2521-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2521">Public Participation is a civic duty, a responsibility&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">montananewbie</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Each year have citizens register of their public participation duty by naming the issue that most interests them.  Through a lottery system select a random sample of a few thousand citizens in places across the nation to deliberate a specific issue.  Convene the random sample of citizens, place them in tables of ten with diverse people, supply them with neutral educational materials and let them deliberate a variety of options to shape pending policy issue.   After small group deliberations among diverse people ask the people to rank order their choices for addressing the issue using audience response system.<br/><br/>Make public participation a responsibility for every citizen to take seriously—like jury duty. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2521" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2521', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2242&topicID=2521')">Comments (5)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2521"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2242">New Strategies and Techniques</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=random participation">random participation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=deliberation">deliberation</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=diversity">diversity</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2521"></div>
